sentence: Olga Guillot (October 9, 1922 – July 12, 2010) was a Cuban singer who was known as the "queen of bolero."
Olga Guillot was born in Santiago de Cuba, and her family moved to Havana, Cuba when she was five years old.
Soon after, Guillot met Miguelito Valdés, who took her to New York City, where Guillot was able to record her first album with the Decca label.
Olga Guillot kept a house in Cuba as she traveled around the world, along with her house in Mexico.
But Guillot opposed Fidel Castro's regime, and in 1962 she decided to leave Cuba for good and establish herself in Venezuela.
During her career, she performed alongside superstars of music such as Frank Sinatra, Sarah Vaughan, and her close friend and fellow Cuban exile, the great Celia Cruz.

During her career, she performed alongside superstars of music such as Frank Sinatra, Sarah Vaughan, and her close friend and fellow Cuban exile, the great Celia Cruz.
She was very good friends with Celia Cruz, whom she often referred to as "(her) sister".
She is survived by one daughter, Olga Maria Touzet-Guillot, born from her relationship with pianist and composer, René Touzet.
